## 1. Get Gemini API Key (Free)

1. Go to [Google AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/apikey)
2. Sign in with your Google account
3. Click **"Create API Key"**
4. Copy the key — you'll need it for the [.env](file:///d:/Prabhu%20V/chatbot-project/backend/.env) file

> [!NOTE]
> The free tier gives you **15 RPM** (requests per minute) and **1 million tokens/day** — more than enough for a chatbot.

---

## 2. DNS Setup (Bigrock)

Log in to your **Bigrock** DNS management panel and add an **A record**:

| Type | Host | Value | TTL |
|------|------|-------|-----|
| A | `neva` | `YOUR_VPS_IP_ADDRESS` | 3600 |

> [!NOTE]
> DNS propagation takes **5–30 min** (sometimes up to 24h). Check with: `nslookup neva.nevas.ai`

---

## 3. SSH into VPS

```bash
ssh root@YOUR_VPS_IP_ADDRESS
```

---

## 4. Install System Dependencies

```bash
# Update system
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# Python 3.12 + build tools
sudo apt install -y python3 python3-pip python3-venv python3-dev \
  build-essential git curl wget libpq-dev

# Node.js 20.x (for building the dashboard)
curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | sudo -E bash -
sudo apt install -y nodejs

# Certbot for SSL
sudo apt install -y certbot python3-certbot-nginx
```

---

## 5. Setup PostgreSQL + pgvector

```bash
# Install PostgreSQL 16
sudo apt install -y postgresql postgresql-contrib

# Install pgvector extension
sudo apt install -y postgresql-16-pgvector
```

Create the database:

```bash
sudo -u postgres psql
```

```sql
CREATE USER neva_user WITH PASSWORD 'YOUR_STRONG_DB_PASSWORD';
CREATE DATABASE neva_chatbot OWNER neva_user;
\c neva_chatbot
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS vector;
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE neva_chatbot TO neva_user;
\q
```

> [!CAUTION]
> Replace `YOUR_STRONG_DB_PASSWORD` with a real secure password.

---

## 6. Clone & Setup Backend

### 6.1 Clone the repository

```bash
sudo mkdir -p /var/www/neva-chatbot
sudo chown $USER:$USER /var/www/neva-chatbot
git clone https://github.com/Nevas-AI/Chatbot.git /var/www/neva-chatbot
cd /var/www/neva-chatbot
```

### 6.2 Setup Python virtual environment

```bash
cd /var/www/neva-chatbot/backend
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip install --upgrade pip
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 6.3 Configure environment variables

```bash
nano .env
```

Update with **production values**:

```env
# ===========================================
# Neva Chatbot - Production Configuration
# ===========================================

WEBSITE_URL=https://nevastech.com

# Company Information
COMPANY_NAME=Nevas Technologies
SUPPORT_EMAIL=info@nevastech.com
SUPPORT_PHONE=+91 0123456789
BUSINESS_HOURS=Mon-Sat 9AM-6PM IST

# Google Gemini API (FREE)
GEMINI_API_KEY=paste_your_gemini_api_key_here
LLM_MODEL=gemini-2.0-flash
EMBEDDING_MODEL=text-embedding-004

# ChromaDB Configuration
CHROMA_PERSIST_DIR=/var/www/neva-chatbot/backend/chroma_db
CHROMA_COLLECTION_NAME=aria_knowledge

# Scraper Configuration
MAX_PAGES=100
AUTO_REFRESH_HOURS=24

# Database (UPDATE PASSWORD!)
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://neva_user:YOUR_STRONG_DB_PASSWORD@localhost:5432/neva_chatbot

# Dashboard Password
DASHBOARD_PASSWORD=YOUR_DASHBOARD_PASSWORD

# Fernet key (generate fresh one below)
FERNET_KEY=GENERATE_NEW_KEY
```

Generate a fresh Fernet key:

```bash
source venv/bin/activate
python3 -c "from cryptography.fernet import Fernet; print(Fernet.generate_key().decode())"
```

Copy the output and paste it as the `FERNET_KEY` value.

### 6.4 Test the backend

```bash
source venv/bin/activate
uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
```

You should see `✅ Database tables created successfully`. Press **Ctrl+C** to stop.

---

## 7. Build the Dashboard

### 7.1 Update Vite base path

The dashboard is served at `/dashboard/`, so update the Vite config:

```bash
nano /var/www/neva-chatbot/dashboard/vite.config.ts
```

Add `base: '/dashboard/'`:

```typescript
export default defineConfig({
  base: '/dashboard/',   // ← Add this line
  plugins: [react(), tailwindcss()],
  server: {
    port: 5173,
    proxy: {
      '/api': {
        target: 'http://localhost:8000',
        changeOrigin: true,
      },
    },
  },
})
```

### 7.2 Build

```bash
cd /var/www/neva-chatbot/dashboard

# Create production env (empty VITE_API_URL = use relative paths)
echo 'VITE_API_URL=' > .env.production

npm install
npm run build
```

---

## 8. Configure Nginx

```bash
sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/neva.nevas.ai
```

Paste:

```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name neva.nevas.ai;

    # === Backend API ===
    location /api/ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8000;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;

        # SSE support (streaming chat)
        proxy_buffering off;
        proxy_cache off;
        proxy_read_timeout 300s;
        proxy_set_header Connection '';
        chunked_transfer_encoding off;
    }

    # === WebSocket (live dashboard updates) ===
    location /api/dashboard/ws/ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8000;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header Connection "upgrade";
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_read_timeout 86400;
    }

    # === Dashboard (Vite static build) ===
    location /dashboard/ {
        alias /var/www/neva-chatbot/dashboard/dist/;
        try_files $uri $uri/ /dashboard/index.html;
    }

    # === Widget JS ===
    location /widget/ {
        alias /var/www/neva-chatbot/widget/;
        add_header Access-Control-Allow-Origin *;
        add_header Cache-Control "public, max-age=3600";
    }

    # === Root redirect ===
    location = / {
        return 301 /dashboard/;
    }

    client_max_body_size 50M;
}
```

Enable and test:

```bash
sudo ln -sf /etc/nginx/sites-available/neva.nevas.ai /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl reload nginx
```

---

## 9. Setup SSL (Let's Encrypt)

```bash
sudo certbot --nginx -d neva.nevas.ai
```

- Enter your email, agree to ToS
- Choose **redirect HTTP → HTTPS** (option 2)

Verify auto-renewal:

```bash
sudo certbot renew --dry-run
```

---

## 10. Create Systemd Service

```bash
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/neva-backend.service
```

```ini
[Unit]
Description=Neva Chatbot Backend (FastAPI + Gemini)
After=network.target postgresql.service

[Service]
Type=simple
User=root
WorkingDirectory=/var/www/neva-chatbot/backend
Environment=PATH=/var/www/neva-chatbot/backend/venv/bin:/usr/bin
ExecStart=/var/www/neva-chatbot/backend/venv/bin/uvicorn main:app --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000 --workers 2
Restart=always
RestartSec=5

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

---

## 11. Start Everything

```bash
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable neva-backend
sudo systemctl start neva-backend

# Verify
sudo systemctl status neva-backend
sudo systemctl status postgresql
sudo systemctl status nginx
```

### Test these URLs in your browser:

| URL | Expected |
|-----|----------|
| `https://neva.nevas.ai/dashboard/` | Dashboard login |
| `https://neva.nevas.ai/api/health` | `{"status": "healthy", ...}` |
| `https://neva.nevas.ai/widget/aria-widget.js` | Widget JS file |

### View logs if needed:

```bash
sudo journalctl -u neva-backend -f       # Backend logs
sudo tail -f /var/log/nginx/error.log     # Nginx errors
```

