## 12. Pushing Updates from Local

On your **local Windows machine**:

```bash
# Navigate to project
cd "d:\Prabhu V\chatbot-project"

# Check changes
git status

# Stage → Commit → Push
git add .
git commit -m "feat: your change description"
git push origin main
```

To push **specific files only**:

```bash
git add backend/rag.py dashboard/src/pages/LeadsPage.tsx
git commit -m "fix: specific fix description"
git push origin main
```

---

## 13. Deploying Updates on VPS

### Option A: Manual steps

```bash
ssh root@YOUR_VPS_IP_ADDRESS

cd /var/www/neva-chatbot
git pull origin main

# If backend changed:
cd backend && source venv/bin/activate && pip install -r requirements.txt && deactivate

# If dashboard changed:
cd /var/www/neva-chatbot/dashboard && npm install && npm run build

# Restart
sudo systemctl restart neva-backend
```

### Option B: One-command deploy script (recommended)

Create the script once:

```bash
sudo nano /var/www/neva-chatbot/deploy.sh
```

```bash
#!/bin/bash
set -e
echo "🚀 Deploying Neva Chatbot..."

cd /var/www/neva-chatbot
echo "📥 Pulling latest code..."
git pull origin main

echo "🐍 Updating backend..."
cd backend
source venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt --quiet
deactivate

echo "🏗️ Building dashboard..."
cd /var/www/neva-chatbot/dashboard
npm install --silent
npm run build

echo "🔄 Restarting backend..."
sudo systemctl restart neva-backend

echo "✅ Done! → https://neva.nevas.ai/dashboard/"
```

```bash
chmod +x /var/www/neva-chatbot/deploy.sh
```

**Deploy from anywhere:**

```bash
ssh root@YOUR_VPS_IP_ADDRESS "/var/www/neva-chatbot/deploy.sh"
```

---

## 📋 Quick Reference

| Task | Command |
|------|---------|
| Check backend | `sudo systemctl status neva-backend` |
| Restart backend | `sudo systemctl restart neva-backend` |
| View logs | `sudo journalctl -u neva-backend -f` |
| Reload Nginx | `sudo systemctl reload nginx` |
| Renew SSL | `sudo certbot renew` |
| Deploy update | `/var/www/neva-chatbot/deploy.sh` |
| Edit .env | `nano /var/www/neva-chatbot/backend/.env` |

